item.title: [PI]Starter book[PI]
item.dc:creator: @Qbix Qbix
item.description:
@Qbix wrote:

If you say so, I find mine to be much worse then his as it uses the quest interface and it is a bit more messy than his. Don’t hate

Client.java

Add this method Thanks to I Vain I (Or at least thats who I got it from)

[code]public void clearQuestInterface() {
for (int element : QuestInterface) {
getPA().sendFrame126("", element);
}
}

public int[] QuestInterface = {8145, 8147, 8148, 8149, 8150, 8151, 8152,
8153, 8154, 8155, 8156, 8157, 8158, 8159, 8160, 8161, 8162, 8163,
8164, 8165, 8166, 8167, 8168, 8169, 8170, 8171, 8172, 8173, 8174,
8175, 8176, 8177, 8178, 8179, 8180, 8181, 8182, 8183, 8184, 8185,
8186, 8187, 8188, 8189, 8190, 8191, 8192, 8193, 8194, 8195, 12174,
12175, 12176, 12177, 12178, 12179, 12180, 12181, 12182, 12183,
12184, 12185, 12186, 12187, 12188, 12189, 12190, 12191, 12192,
12193, 12194, 12195, 12196, 12197, 12198, 12199, 12200, 12201,
12202, 12203, 12204, 12205, 12206, 12207, 12208, 12209, 12210,
12211, 12212, 12213, 12214, 12215, 12216, 12217, 12218, 12219,
12220, 12221, 12222, 12223};[/code]

And then add this method which is a basic quest interface.

public void starterBook() { getPA().sendFrame126("YOUR TITLE HERE", 8144); clearQuestInterface(); getPA().sendFrame126("BOOK TEXT", 8145); getPA().sendFrame126("BOOK TEXT", 8147); getPA().sendFrame126("BOOK TEXT", 8148); getPA().sendFrame126("etc....", 8149); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8150); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8151); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8152); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8153); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8154); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8155); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8156); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8157); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8158); getPA().sendFrame126("", 8159); getPA().showInterface(8134); }

Then go into ClickItem.java and add this

if(itemId == 1856) { c.starterBook(); c.startAnimation(1350); }

Add the item 1856 to your starter and your done.
